        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(gemini): bridge OAuth profiles into CLI runtime",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- opt `google-gemini-cli` into explicit OpenClaw auth-profile forwarding\n- refresh/load the selected OAuth profile before CLI backend preparation\n- materialize selected Gemini OAuth credentials into an isolated `GEMINI_CLI_HOME/.gemini/oauth_creds.json` for the `gemini` subprocess\n- keep Gemini CLI auth epochs profile-owned when the bridge is active\n\nFixes #88742.\n\n## Proof\n\nHEAD: `c6797c3ddd5469f32ec4d7d9b59f8e795fcf4b28`\n\nValidation log: `/tmp/openclaw-pr88742-validation.log`\n\nCommands:\n\n```bash\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/google/setup-api.test.ts src/agents/cli-backends.test.ts src/agents/command/attempt-execution.cli.test.ts --reporter=dot\npnpm -s exec oxfmt --check extensions/google/cli-backend.ts extensions/google/setup-api.test.ts src/agents/cli-backends.test.ts src/agents/cli-backends.ts src/agents/cli-runner/prepare.ts src/agents/command/attempt-execution.cli.test.ts src/agents/command/attempt-execution.ts src/plugin-sdk/cli-backend.ts src/plugins/cli-backend.types.ts src/plugins/types.ts\npnpm -s exec oxlint --tsconfig config/tsconfig/oxlint.core.json src/agents/cli-backends.test.ts src/agents/cli-backends.ts src/agents/cli-runner/prepare.ts src/agents/command/attempt-execution.cli.test.ts src/agents/command/attempt-execution.ts src/plugin-sdk/cli-backend.ts src/plugins/cli-backend.types.ts src/plugins/types.ts extensions/google/cli-backend.ts extensions/google/setup-api.test.ts\ngit diff --check\n```\n\nRelevant output:\n\n```text\nTest Files  2 passed (2)\nTests  59 passed (59)\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\nTests  3 passed (3)\nAll matched files use the correct format.\n```\n\nSource-level behavior proof: `/tmp/openclaw-pr88742-proof.log`\n\n- `extensions/google/setup-api.test.ts` proves selected OAuth credentials produce an isolated Gemini CLI home and writes `.gemini/oauth_creds.json` without logging token material.\n- `src/agents/command/attempt-execution.cli.test.ts` proves canonical `google/*` models routed through `google-gemini-cli` select the `google-gemini-cli:*` auth profile before `runCliAgent`.\n\nNot tested:\n\n- Full `pnpm -s exec tsgo --noEmit` is blocked on current HEAD by pre-existing errors outside this patch:\n\n```text\nsrc/config/io.ts(192,7): error TS2527: The inferred type of 'configWritePostCommitRollback' references an inaccessible 'unique symbol' type. A type annotation is necessary.\nsrc/secrets/config-io.ts(8,17): error TS4058: Return type of exported function has or is using name 'configWritePostCommitRollback' from external module \".../src/config/io\" but cannot be named.\n```\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior or issue addressed**: `google-gemini-cli` backend preparation receives a selected OpenClaw `google-gemini-cli:*` OAuth profile, materializes that OAuth profile into an isolated `GEMINI_CLI_HOME/.gemini/oauth_creds.json`, and passes that isolated home to the real `gemini` subprocess instead of relying on ambient `~/.gemini` state.\n- **Real environment tested**: Local Linux workstation, PR branch `fix/88742-gemini-cli-oauth-bridge`, head `ada77084fb0bce5ccb88ba88b38ed803b5b9f0c6`, OpenClaw `2026.5.31 (7150977)`, `@google/gemini-cli` binary available as `/usr/local/bin/gemini`, real Gemini CLI version `0.40.1`. Token values and account identifiers were not printed.\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch**:\n\n```text\ncd /home/rev/projects/openclaw-prs/pr-88742-gemini-cli-oauth-bridge\npnpm install\npnpm build\nconfirmed backend registration path:\n  rg -n 'buildGoogleGeminiCliBackend|prepareExecution|CliBackendPlugin|cliBackends' src packages extensions/google | head -120\n  nl -ba extensions/google/cli-backend.ts | sed -n '1,155p'\ncreated direct backend proof harness:\n  .tmp-pr88748-gemini-backend-proof.mts\nran:\n  BAD_HOME=/tmp/tmp.6jUzYBOeWy PROFILE='google-gemini-cli:jason.allen.oneal@gmail.com' pnpm exec tsx ./.tmp-pr88748-gemini-backend-proof.mts 2>&1 | tee /tmp/pr88748-direct-backend-proof.log\nsanitized:\n  sed -E -e 's/ya29\\.[A-Za-z0-9._-]+/<redacted-access-token>/g' -e 's#1//[A-Za-z0-9._-]+#<redacted-refresh-token>#g' -e 's/eyJ[A-Za-z0-9._-]+/<redacted-jwt>/g' -e 's/AIza[[:alnum:]_-]+/<redacted-google-api-key>/g' /tmp/pr88748-direct-backend-proof.log > /tmp/pr88748-direct-backend-proof.redacted.log\nverified no obvious token material remained:\n  grep -E 'ya29\\.|1//|eyJ|AIza' /tmp/pr88748-direct-backend-proof.redacted.log\n```\n\n- **Evidence after fix**:\n\n```text\n=== PR 88748 direct Gemini CLI backend proof ===\nbackend_id=google-gemini-cli\nprofile=google-gemini-cli:jason.allen.oneal@gmail.com\nbad_parent_GEMINI_CLI_HOME=/tmp/tmp.6jUzYBOeWy\nprepared_GEMINI_CLI_HOME=/tmp/openclaw/gemini-cli-home-m4iizB\nprepared_home_is_bad_parent=false\nhome_mode=700\ngemini_dir_mode=700\noauth_creds_path=/tmp/openclaw/gemini-cli-home-m4iizB/.gemini/oauth_creds.json\noauth_creds_mode=600\noauth_creds_shape={\"has_access_token\":true,\"has_refresh_token\":true,\"has_expiry_date\":true,\"token_type\":\"Bearer\",\"has_id_token\":false}\nreal_gemini_exit=0\nreal_gemini_stdout=0.40.1\nreal_gemini_stderr=\ncleanup_removed_home=true\n```\n\n- **Observed result after fix**: `buildGoogleGeminiCliBackend().prepareExecution(...)` accepted a `google-gemini-cli` OAuth profile, created a private isolated Gemini CLI home, wrote `.gemini/oauth_creds.json` with Bearer OAuth credential shape and restrictive file permissions, returned a `GEMINI_CLI_HOME` different from the deliberately bad parent home, and a real `gemini` subprocess started successfully with that prepared environment. Cleanup removed the isolated home afterward.\n- **What was not tested**: The proof intentionally did not print raw Google OAuth access tokens, refresh tokens, ID tokens, or private account data. The subprocess proof used `gemini --version` to prove the real Gemini CLI binary starts under the prepared `GEMINI_CLI_HOME`.\n\n## ClawSweeper follow-up\n\n- Privatized the Gemini credential bridge again: removed `CliBackendAuthProfileCredential`, `authCredential`, `acceptsAuthProfileForwarding`, and `resolveAuthProfileForExecution` from the public Plugin SDK/CLI backend type surface.\n- Kept the selected-profile bridge scoped to the bundled `google-gemini-cli` runtime path, where the runner passes the credential through a private extension context only after selecting/refreshing the OpenClaw profile.\n- Verified no public references remain:\n\n```text\nrg -n \"acceptsAuthProfileForwarding|resolveAuthProfileForExecution|CliBackendAuthProfileCredential\" src extensions/google docs\n# no matches\nrg -n \"authCredential\" src/plugin-sdk src/plugins/cli-backend.types.ts src/plugins/types.ts\n# no matches\n```\n\n### Authenticated Gemini prompt proof after bridge privacy fix\n\nRedacted log: `/tmp/pr88748-authenticated-gemini-prompt.redacted.log`\n\nCommand shape:\n\n```text\nBAD_HOME=$(mktemp -d) pnpm -s exec tsx --eval '<source-level backend proof harness>' 2>&1 \\\n  | sed -E -e 's/ya29\\.[A-Za-z0-9._-]+/<redacted-access-token>/g' \\\n           -e 's#1//[A-Za-z0-9._-]+#<redacted-refresh-token>#g' \\\n           -e 's/eyJ[A-Za-z0-9._-]+/<redacted-jwt>/g' \\\n           -e 's/AIza[[:alnum:]_-]+/<redacted-google-api-key>/g' \\\n  | tee /tmp/pr88748-authenticated-gemini-prompt.redacted.log\n```\n\nEvidence:\n\n```text\n=== PR 88748 authenticated Gemini CLI prompt proof ===\nbackend_id=google-gemini-cli\nprofile=google-gemini-cli:default\nmodel=gemini-3.1-flash-lite\nbad_parent_GEMINI_CLI_HOME=/tmp/tmp.O2CB9ihmwO\nprepared_GEMINI_CLI_HOME=/tmp/openclaw/gemini-cli-home-d0HCiz\nprepared_home_is_bad_parent=false\nreal_gemini_prompt_exit=0\nreal_gemini_prompt_stdout_begin\n{\n  \"session_id\": \"463ff78c-cf21-42b4-b8cc-4172073d97a7\",\n  \"response\": \"PR88748_AUTH_OK\",\n  \"stats\": {\n    \"models\": {\n      \"gemini-3.1-flash-lite\": {\n        \"api\": {\n          \"totalRequests\": 1,\n          \"totalErrors\": 0,\n          \"totalLatencyMs\": 1359\n        },\n        \"tokens\": {\n          \"input\": 13771,\n          \"prompt\": 13771,\n          \"candidates\": 10,\n          \"total\": 13781,\n          \"cached\": 0,\n          \"thoughts\": 0,\n          \"tool\": 0\n        }\n      }\n    },\n    \"tools\": {\n      \"totalCalls\": 0,\n      \"totalSuccess\": 0,\n      \"totalFail\": 0\n    }\n  }\n}\nreal_gemini_prompt_stdout_end\nreal_gemini_prompt_stderr=Warning: Basic terminal detected (TERM=dumb). Visual rendering will be limited. For the best experience, use a terminal emulator with truecolor support.\nWarning: 256-color support not detected. Using a terminal with at least 256-color support is recommended for a better visual experience.\nRipgrep is not available. Falling back to GrepTool.\n```\n\nSanitization check:\n\n```text\ngrep -E 'ya29\\.|1//|eyJ|AIza' /tmp/pr88748-authenticated-gemini-prompt.redacted.log\n# no matches\n```\n",
